tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE PerformanceMetrics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(50),
    accuracy FLOAT,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT,
    f1_score FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE model_performance_metrics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(50),
    accuracy DECIMAL(5, 2),
    precision DECIMAL(5, 2),
    recall DECIMAL(5, 2)
);

CREATE TABLE model_evaluation_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    actual_class INT,
    predicted_class INT,
    probability DECIMAL(5, 2),
    evaluation_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE performance_metrics (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    accuracy FLOAT,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE model_evaluation (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    evaluation_date DATE,
    metric_name VARCHAR,
    metric_value FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE model_details (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    model_name VARCHAR,
    training_data_size INT,
    testing_data_size INT
);

CREATE TABLE ModelMetrics (
    model_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    accuracy FLOAT,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE ModelMetrics (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(100),
    dataset_name VARCHAR(100),
    accuracy DOUBLE PRECISION
);

CREATE TABLE TrainingData (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    data_point INT,
    feature_1 DOUBLE PRECISION,
    feature_2 DOUBLE PRECISION,
    feature_3 DOUBLE PRECISION
);

CREATE TABLE EvaluationResults (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    evaluation_date DATE,
    precision_score DOUBLE PRECISION,
    recall_score DOUBLE PRECISION,
    f1_score DOUBLE PRECISION
);

CREATE TABLE Hyperparameters (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    learning_rate DOUBLE PRECISION,
    batch_size INT,
    epochs INT
);

CREATE TABLE ModelParameters (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    parameter_name VARCHAR(100),
    parameter_value DOUBLE PRECISION
);
